catstats.name: catstats
catstats.help:
Returns the specified unit’s stats.
 All EoC treasures are assumed complete.

udpcat.name: udpcat
udpcat.brief: Returns the UDP entry of a cat.
udpcat.help: Returns the UDP entry of an Uber Rare Cat.

udpcard.name: udpcard
udpcard.brief: Returns the UDP entry card of a cat.
udpcard.help: Returns the UDP entry card of an Uber Rare Cat.

enemystats.name: enemystats
enemystats.help: The third parameter allows you to specify magnifications for attack and health separately (the first parameter being used for health), though split magnifications are only used for baron bosses in-game. If this parameter is left blank, the second parameter will be used for both attack and health.

renamecat.name: renamecat
renamecat.brief: Creates an alias for a unit
renamecat.help: Creates an alias (custom name) to use instead of the real name when using a command for a unit.

renameenemy.name: renameenemy
renameenemy.brief: Creates an alias for a enemy
renameenemy.help: Creates an alias (custom name) to use instead of the real name when using a command for an enemy.

renamestage.name: renamestage
renamestage.brief: Creates an alias for a stage
renamestage.help: Creates an alias (custom name) to use instead of the real name when using a command for a stage.

catnamesof.name: catnamesof
catnamesof.brief: Returns all custom names for the specified cat unit.

enemynamesof.name: enemynamesof
enemynamesof.brief: Returns all custom names for the specified enemy unit.

stagenamesof.name: stagenamesof
stagenamesof.brief: Returns all custom names for the specified stage.

stage.name: stage
stage.brief: Returns the schematics of the specified stage.
stage.help:
Returns the schematics of the specified stage. 
 The second and third parameters are optional, though they may be necessary to use if multiple stages have similar names, which is the case for certain enigma stages. You can skip the difficulty of the stage in its title, as seen in the last example.
examples: !sb The Big Bang; CotC Ch.2; CH

whereis.name: whereis
whereis.brief: Returns all stages where the specified enemy/ies appear.
whereis.help:
Returns all stages where the specified enemy appears.
 Specify multiple enemies to return every stage where all of them appear.
examples: !whereis JK Bun Bun; Capy; Those Guys

whereisb.name: whereisb
whereisb.brief: Returns all stages where the specified enemy/ies appear as an embed.
whereisb.help:
Returns all stages where the specified enemy appears as an embed.
 Specify multiple enemies to return every stage where all of them appear.
examples: !whereisb JK Bun Bun; Capy; Those Guys

whereismonthly.name: whereismonthly
whereismonthly.brief: Returns all stages where the specified enemy/ies appear, sorted by energy cost.
whereismonthly.help:
Returns all stages where the specified enemy appears (sorted in ascending order of energy cost).
 Specify multiple enemies to return every stage where all of them appear.
examples: !whereismonthly JK Bun Bun; Capy; Those Guys

comboname.name: comboname
comboname.brief: Returns data of the named CatCombo.
comboname.help: Returns the specified CatCombo’s full name, the units needed to activate it, and its effect.

combowith.name: combowith
combowith.brief: Returns all combos the specified unit is a part of.
combowith.help:
Returns all combos the specified unit is a part of. 
 This command is form-sensitive, meaning that __if you specify a unit’s first form, combos that require its 2nd or 3rd form will not be shown.__

cst.name: cst
cst.brief: Returns stats for talented Cat units
cst.help:
Returns the specified unit’s stats, with support for talents. All EoC treasures are assumed complete. 
 The order for talents is listed below the stats when the command is used without arguments. 
 Entering a non-integer level makes it default to the highest level. Entering a negative level makes it default to 0.

talentsof.name: talentsof
talentsof.brief: Returns talents of the given Cat unit
talentsof.help: Returns the talents of the given Cat unit, with NP Costs, and thier effects.

sayhi.name: sayhi
sayhi.brief: Responds to you based on your privilege level

say.name: say
say.brief: CatBot sends your message to the channel with the given ID.
